NewsBoard.Title: Karim Benzema: “I want to retire here”
NewsBoard.Content: BLD Real Madrid has opened a farewell ceremony for striker Karim Benzema after 14 matches for the Santiago Bernabeu team. President Perez thanked Benzema for his commitment to his career as he was just beginning to emerge as one of the potential strikers of French football from the moment he arrived at Real Madrid. After 14 games for Real Madrid, Karim Benzema is leaving with the status of a legend that Real once owned along with countless titles. According to Football-Espana, Benzema also expressed his feelings about the memories at Real Madrid: Thank you very much Real Madrid. It has been a good journey in my life. I was fortunate to realize my childhood dream thanks to the president. When I saw you, I said 'he's the one who brought in Ronaldo and Zidane. He is extraordinary. Today is the time to go see another story. The most important thing for me is that everything I win, I enjoy as a child. As I said in my presentation 'one, two and three, hala Madrid! In addition, he also thanked coach Carlo Ancelotti at the farewell ceremony of the club Also thanks to Ancelotti, who gave me confidence from the beginning. I have learned a lot with you. It's a little sad that I'm leaving my club. I signed a contract with Madrid and I wanted to retire here, but that was not the case. I will always be a Madrid fan. Thank you also to the fans for always giving me strength. Sincere thanks to all of you.” Either way, Benzema left Real Madrid as one of the greatest strikers they've ever had. Along with the countless titles that Benzema won with the White Vulture, he deserves to be considered a legend in the legendary temple of the Royal Spanish football team.

NewsBoard.Title: FC Barcelona successful recruitment Ousmane Dembele
NewsBoard.Content: PSG have parted ways with Lionel Messi on a free transfer, they are also facing the possibility of losing more Kylian Mbappe. The French striker only has a contract until 2024 but has refused to extend it, if he does not sell the player born in 1998 in the summer of this year, the Paris team may lose everything on a free transfer next summer. PSG is actively negotiating to bring in a quality name to replace the French striker. The chosen one was none other than his countryman, Ousmane Dembele. Rumors have only appeared, but the probability of it happening is extremely high. Barcelona coach Xavi himself has confirmed his student will leave the club to join PSG. According to some sources, Ousmane Dembele will join PSG this week after the Paris team paid the full €50 million in contract termination fee for Barca. Most recently, on his personal page, transfer expert Fabrizio Romano gave Ousmane Dembele's transfer to PSG. He wrote: Ousmane Dembele arrives at PSG, Medical examinations are underway, contract valid until June 2028 will be signed on Saturday. PSG spent 50 million euros to release Dembele's contract with Barca, they also took a large fee for the player's agent, Moussa Sissoko. In addition, PSG will certainly have to provide the French player with a very high salary.

NewsBoard.Title: Neuer had a serious problem, did not set a date for re-export
NewsBoard.Content: After saying goodbye to the 2022 World Cup right from the group stage, goalkeeper Manuel Neuer had bad luck and was forced to stop playing for the end of the 2022-2023 season. Accordingly, the goalkeeper of the German team and Bayern Munich broke his leg while skiing during the breathing after the second forgettable World Cup in his career. Neuer subsequently underwent surgery and has returned to training with the Bayern first team in recent months. According to German newspaper BILD, Neuer is having difficulty 'kick the ball properly'. Therefore he had to undergo another surgery for the problem. The 37-year-old goalkeeper suffered a severe fracture in his right leg, which caused problems when kicking the ball with his left foot and the other as a support. The leading German newspaper reported that Neuer also had problems jumping up and catching the ball, because his injured leg limited his reach. Before the current situation, it is not excluded that the German goalkeeper has to sit out for up to 10 weeks. In the context of Neuer not setting a return date, Bayern Munich is said to be targeting Wojciech Szczesny. The Polish goalkeeper has become the Bundesliga champions' first choice to replace Yann Sommer, who is about to move to Inter Milan. According to Mail Sport, Juventus is ready to sell the Polish goalkeeper before the interest from the Gray Lobster. In addition to Szczesny, the Bundesliga representative also targeted Chelsea goalkeeper Kepa Arrizabalaga.

NewsBoard.Title: Nkunku On the operating table, 4 months out of competition
NewsBoard.Content: Chelsea update Nkunku's injury Christopher Nkunku's injury in the match against Dortmund was much more serious than expected. The French player suffered a meniscus injury. According to the latest announcement from Chelsea, Nkunku even had to undergo surgery. The surgery has just been successful and the striker born in 1997 will begin the recovery process. The Chelsea side did not update the details of the time Nkunku will have to leave the pitch. But according to journalist Fabrizio Romano, the Blues rookie will have to take a break from playing for at least 4 months. Nkunku's injury is definitely news for Chelsea when the new season is only a few days away from officially kicking off. The Blues spent £ 60 million to recruit the 26-year-old striker in the summer of 2023 from Leipzig in the hope of strengthening the attack power. And Nkunku integrated very quickly with the new team. In the last tour, the French striker scored 3 goals in 5 matches. With Nkunku seriously injured, it is almost certain that Chelsea will be forced to add a striker for the rest of the summer transfer window of 2023. Dusan Vlahovic and most recently Neymar are on the list of transfer targets in attack. by The Blues.

NewsBoard.Title: HLV Ten Hag get privileges that Mourinho and Van Gaal don't have
NewsBoard.Content: The leadership of the Red Devils recently arranged a dedicated area for coach Ten Hag's teachers and students before the match. This is a request from the Dutch strategist. This will be useful technically, but will affect the team's revenue. Previously, Suite 7 in the South Stand was used for fans, bringing the club more than £10 million in revenue. Now, it is used by the players before each match. Louis van Gaal - the coach appointed by Man United in 2014 and has been with the club for two years - and his successor, Jose Mourinho both made this request but were not met by the team's leadership. The special usually gathers his team at the Lowry Hotel in the city center, but has difficulty getting to the stadium due to congestion. Ten Hag's promising first season has given the former Ajax manager more say. The removal of part of the stadium to host the fans into a player lounge is proof of the 'football first' approach led by new chief executive Richard Arnold.

NewsBoard.Title: Man City announced central defender Gvardiol
NewsBoard.Content: Man City recruited the second rookie in the summer of 2023, the 21-year-old midfielder Josko Gvardiol for a transfer fee of $ 99 million. In a video posted on Man City's Twitter page today, August 5, coach Pep Guardiola writes on the whiteboard in the dressing room the words Guardiola, then changes the u into a v, then deletes the a at the end. That text turned into Gvardiol, then the video showed the 21-year-old Croatian midfielder smiling. Welcome Josko, Man City wrote. Gvardiol in Croatian means guard, similar to guardiola in Spanish. Even the Croatian name Josko is derived from Josep - Guardiola's name in Latin. In the press conference on August 4, Guardiola also joked that the new Man City has a very beautiful name. According to Athletic, Man City must pay Leipzig 90 million euros ($99 million) for Gvardiol's transfer fee, making him the second most expensive defender in history after Harry Maguire $ 102 million. He signed a five-year contract with Man City, valid until the summer of 2028. Gvardiol was born on January 23, 2002 in Zagreb, grew up with his hometown club Dinamo. Becoming the club's mainstay at the age of 18, he caught the eye of Leipzig and was recruited by this club for a transfer fee of 21 million USD. The 1.85-meter-tall centre-back played prominently in the Bundesliga, but his value skyrocketed thanks to his performances at the 2022 World Cup with Croatia. Gvardiol is considered the best defender in the tournament, despite being surpassed by Lionel Messi in the semi-finals. He entered the World Team of the Year in 2022 voted by IFFHS.

NewsBoard.Title: The latest move, Liverpool is about to explode the 50 million deal
NewsBoard.Content: After parting ways with Jordan Henderson and Fabinho, Liverpool want to add a midfielder this summer. The Kop hopes to recruit Southampton's Romeo Lavia, but this is an extremely difficult deal. The Anfield team has closed 3 offers to the Championship club. The latest offer hits the £46 million mark, but The Saints are still not satisfied with that figure. Southampton are determined to stand their ground when they want to receive a fee of £ 50 million. In the context of Liverpool still struggling to find a way to convince a partner, the latest information shows that Lavia is likely to leave. Sky Sports have confirmed the 19-year-old was not in Southampton's squad when they met Gillingham in the Carabao Cup. According to Belgian journalist Sacha Tavolieri, Lavia also missed training in the morning, with the player's agent looking to close the deal today. This information raised suspicions that the former Manchester City star broke up with the host club when Liverpool was flirting with him. If Lavia plays in the first round of the Carabao Cup against Gillingham, he will not be eligible for the next matches in this arena for Liverpool in the 2023/24 season.

NewsBoard.Title: AC Milan prepare to extend further with Olivier Giroud
NewsBoard.Content: BLD AC Milan said that it has reached a preliminary agreement with striker Giroud after the great contribution of the French striker in AC Milan shirt this season. According to Fabrizio Romano, the agreement between Giroud and AC Milan was agreed many weeks ago and will be extended until June 2024. In Serie A 2022/2023, Giroud contributed with 8 goals and 4 assists after a total of 26 matches. to play for AC Milan. In particular, in this year's Champions League, the striker born in 1986 also made a mark with 8 goals after 10 matches and with AC Milan reached the Champions League semi-finals after defeating Napoli at dawn this morning. In that match, Giroud also had a goal to help AC Milan beat Napoli with a total score of 2-1 after 2 matches, helping AC Milan reach the semi-finals of the Champions League for the first time in 7 years. Joined AC Milan in July 2021 from Chelsea on a two-year contract. In the first season of 2020/2021 playing under AC Milan, Giroud and the team won Serie A after 11 years of waiting and now it is time to reach the semi-finals of the Champions League with AC Milan. Despite turning 37 years old, Giroud still shows his ability to score goals and enthusiasm when given the opportunity..

NewsBoard.Title: Tottenham spend £ 43 million to welcome Wolfsburg midfielder
NewsBoard.Content: Spurs sẽ trả trước 34,5 triệu Bảng cho Wolfsburg để có được trung vệ Micky van de Ven. Trong hợp đồng có điều khoản phụ trị giá 8,5 triệu Bảng. Van de Ven ký hợp đồng 6 năm với Spurs. Đây là hợp đồng dài nhất của Spurs kể từ trường hợp của Tanguy Ndombele năm 2019. Như vậy, Van de Ven sẽ thi đấu ở Tottenham đến năm 209. Van de Ven sẽ khoác áo số 37 ở Spurs. Anh là tân binh thứ 4 của đội bóng thành London hè này sau James Maddison, Guglielmo Vicario và Manor Solomon. Chuyên gia bóng đá Kevin Hatchard đã có nhận định về Van de Ven trên tờ Sky Sports: “Cậu ấy rất nhanh nhẹn với một trung vệ và có tốc độ lui về rất tốt. Cậu ấy là một cầu thủ quyết liệt và vẫn đang học hỏi bóng đá ở cấp độ cao nhất, và điều này có thể hiểu được. Cách đây không lâu, cậu ấy còn ở Volendam, ngoài Eredivisie và cậu ấy còn không có được suất đá chính ở đó. Nhưng cậu ấy có sức chiến đấu rất mãnh liệt. Ajax nhìn thấy điểm đó và rất muốn có cậu ấy nhưng Wolfsburg đã có mặt trước. Điều thú vị về Van de Ven là cậu ấy được thi đấu rất nhiều dưới thời Niko Kovac. Ông ấy là một HLV dày dạn kinh nghiệm và có tư duy phòng ngự. Ông ấy sẵn sàng sử dụng Van de Ven trong hầu hết mọi trận đấu. Cậu ấy thuận chân trái và rất giỏi đưa bóng thoát khỏi áp lực. Về mặt tiềm năng, Van de Ven có trần rất cao”.

NewsBoard.Title: Arsenal successfully signed goalkeeper David Raya from Brentford
NewsBoard.Content: Raya's arrival means Arsenal secure a long-term goal. They made many offers for the Spain international in the summer of 2020, but were unable to reach an agreement with Brentford. Earlier in the summer, Raya made it clear he would not extend his contract beyond next year having been targeted by Tottenham, but they were unwilling to accommodate Brentford's demands. Manchester United and Chelsea have also been monitoring his situation, but with Brentford having signed Mark Flekken from Freiburg to replace him that puts him at risk of starting the 2023-24 season. According to the Guardian, the Spaniard will replace Matt Turner's reserve keeper when he will leave Arsenal for Nottingham Forest in a deal worth £10m. Though he is unlikely to take the #2 position that his predecessor had to accept. The emergence of such expensive competition, which has pushed Arsenal's spending this summer to £240m, is sure to put Aaron Ramsdale's future in doubt. Arsenal's goalkeeping coach, Iñaki Caña, worked closely with Raya during his time at Brentford. Arteta can feel that two high-quality goalkeepers, both recruited for distribution and will be needed for dual duties in the Premier League and Champions League. Arsenal aim to sell more players in the pre-season to recoup some of their spending and have rejected an offer from Monaco for striker Folarin Balogun, whom they are believed to be valued at around $50 million. board. Internazionale was among others interested in Balogun.

NewsBoard.Title: Newcastle spent £ 43 million for Juventus striker
NewsBoard.Content: During Newcastle's pursuit of AC Milan's Sandro Tonali, reports say The Magpies have also had their eye on other potential Series A targets. And one of the players on manager Eddie Howe's radar is one of them. Federico Chiesa, winger on the Juventus payroll. The Italian striker intends to leave Turin this summer, following the collapse of Max Allegri's empire. And Newcastle is a club that has been strongly linked with 25-year-old talent in recent years, although before that, the Premier League representative had prioritized Harvey Barnes of Leicester City. After successfully recruiting Barnes, Newcastle immediately turned around. with the Chiesa deal. And recently, according to a source from Tuttosport, Chick is willing to spend £ 43 million and an additional fee to own this player. It is known that in addition to the home team of St. James's Park, Aston Villa also wants to spend money to acquire Juve's star. Meanwhile, many teams in the Saudi Pro League have already put Chiesa on the target list and have sent in a number of offers. However, the Italian guy turned it down because he wanted to play at the top level in Europe. And with a place in the Champions League next season, Newcastle becomes an attractive destination for this versatile player.

NewsBoard.Title: Goalkeeper Martinez: 'I will bring Messi to Aston Villa'
NewsBoard.Content: Goalkeeper Emiliano Martinez is displeased with the behavior of PSG fans towards Argentina teammate Lionel Messi. If Messi gets whistled, I'll take him back to Aston Villa, Martinez told ESPN on May 22. I'll connect him with my teammates. I'll make him a barbecue every weekend, have everyone make little flags cheering him on and he'll have a good time. If necessary, I will reduce my salary for Messi. Martinez has been close to Messi since playing for Argentina. At the 2022 World Cup, he became a solid support for his teammates. In the penalty shootout of the quarter-final against the Netherlands and the final against France, the Aston Villa goalkeeper helped Argentina win 4-3 and 4-2. The thing I learned the most from the World Cup is the calm attitude when I want to win, Martinez said. It was thanks to the pressure I had against the Netherlands and France. I've been through many challenges and now I'm more experienced. This season, Aston Villa is making strong progress. From the 19th place after the first five rounds of the Premier League, Martinez and his teammates went to seventh after the penultimate round. If they defend their position in the final round, they will win tickets to the Conference League. The relationship between Messi and the fans of the current club, PSG, has deteriorated since the 2022 World Cup. After PSG lost to Bayern in the 1/8 Champions League round, French fans began to criticize the Argentine striker. The group of crazy fans often whistles when Messi plays at the Parc des Princes home ground. On May 2, PSG suspended Messi for two weeks, because he went to Saudi Arabia without permission. After that, the Argentine striker publicly apologized to the fans and the club. He explained that he thought he would have a day off as usual after the match against Lorient. Messi also said that he could not postpone going to Saudi Arabia, because he postponed once. This season Messi has contributed 20 goals and 20 assists in 39 games for PSG, only 40 goals and nine assists behind Kylian Mbappe. PSG currently leads Ligue 1 with 84 points from 36 games, six points ahead of second-placed Lens. Messi and his teammates only need one point in the last two games to win the title for the second time in a row. At the 2022 World Cup, Messi contributed seven goals and three assists. In addition to the championship, he won the World Cup Golden Ball and Silver Shoe titles. Mbappe won the Golden Shoe with eight goals, while Martinez won the Golden Glove. The contract between Messi and PSG is only valid until the end of June 2023. According to European media, during the summer transfer window, the 35-year-old striker faces the possibility of returning to Barca, to Saudi Arabia or to the US. According to Mundo Deportivo, Messi will bring about $ 260 million in revenue from sponsorship and ticket sales each season for Barca, if he returns. Meanwhile, Barca only had to spend 15 million salary.
